{
  "stem": "21812.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And-- but even if it hadn't, just the idea of, of living under, under the Nazis was enough to make you leave as quickly as possible. so we explored every, every possibility.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "When I say we, it was my parents who did it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And Shanghai took in people.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Cuba took in people.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But these places opened up all of a sudden and then closed down again very quickly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So if you weren't there at the right moment, or didn't whatever, didn't have enough money, in some way deposit an awful lot of money to get there, you, you didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And so that didn't work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my mother wanted to-- and my parents wanted me to be safe.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so my mother wrote to-- my mother, who spoke English fairly well and wrote English well, better then even than she spoke, went to the-- did what a lot of people had done.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Go to the telephone company and get-- that's where you-- who had the telephone books of different nations.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And people would-- who would want to come to the United States would-- we knew people who had written hundreds and hundreds of letters appealing to strangers to send them an affidavit.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- but she only got 10, 10 telephone numbers in England.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she got the numbers of garment manufacturers, assuming that they were Jewish, and two answered.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "A Jewish man in Manchester answered.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you had to-- they had to deposit 200 pounds, which was the equivalent of $1,000 in those days.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they had to guarantee the stay of the child.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he said he would be able to take me in, but he could not deposit the money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And a Mr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "George of Bradford, England, said, yes.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
